<p itemprop="description">A lead graphic designer leads the visual design function across the organisation, setting strategic direction for visual design approaches and ensuring user-centred design principles are embedded throughout all visual communications and interfaces. They manage graphic design teams and drive organisational design excellence.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define and implement visual design strategy across the entire organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead and manage graphic design teams and visual design specialists</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish visual design governance, standards, and brand frameworks</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Champion accessible and inclusive design at executive level</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build strategic partnerships with design and creative communities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Oversee design capability development and training programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in visual design tools, techniques, and methodologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure design excellence and user focus across all organisational programmes</li>
    </ul>
</section>

